---
description: Test coins are local-only and not real payments
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

The app includes TEST COINS used only for testing gift interactions and UI behavior.

These test coins are NOT real currency and must never be treated as real payments.

STRICT RULES:

Test coins purpose:
- used only for testing gifts
- used only for UI/UX testing
- used as temporary score/points
- used to simulate gifting behavior

Strictly forbidden:
- do not connect test coins to IAP (Google/Apple)
- do not connect test coins to Stripe
- do not connect test coins to any payment system
- do not persist test coins as real balance in production database
- do not mix test coins with real coins
- do not use test coins in real wallet logic
- do not allow test coins to trigger real transactions
- do not send test coin events to production payment backend
- do not treat test coins as real revenue or value

Separation rules:
- keep test coins completely separate from real coin balance
- use separate state/variable for test coins (e.g. testCoins)
- never merge testCoins with realCoins
- never subtract from real balance when using test coins
- never add test coins to real wallet

Allowed:
- simulate sending gifts using test coins
- trigger gift animations with test coins
- simulate leaderboard or score using test coins
- use local state or temporary storage for test coins
- reset test coins freely without affecting real data
- use test coins in development or testing mode

Implementation rules:
- prefer local state or isolated store for test coins
- clearly label test coin logic in code
- keep test coin logic simple and removable
- do not build critical app logic depending on test coins

Default behavior:
test coins are fake, local, isolated, and only for testing gifts.
